rename.to: [FR] Tool to migrate file backend to SQL

body: @Casyfill This sounds like a very reasonable feature. Is this something you'd be willing to work on / submit a PR for? Cc'ing @amesar, who has some context on migrating between stores.
It's not a priority for my team, but I'll try to find time to work on this a bit later.

Are there any best practices on how to do this without this tool? 

Currently, I am thinking of iterating over the file backend with a python script and recreating all the experiments, metrics, parameters and artifacts.

@pietermarsman any chance you can share the script?

I suspect another option would be to pull all records from the mlflow itself via API, then batch-add them via API
I was not yet forced to take this route, so the script does not exist yet. Using the API (with 2 parallel connections?) sounds easier / less error-prone.

@pietermarsman  I've recently started the migration 0.8.1 -> 1.8.0 and wrote the following script (based on someones)  
https://gist.github.com/weldpua2008/7f0c4644d247bd0fc7ba9a83c2d337d5
P.S.
I guess it's better to use mlflow native functions or APi same as https://github.com/amesar/mlflow-tools/blob/master/mlflow_tools/export_import/copy_experiment.py

For Model Registry, I can think of two acceptable options:  

1. Add the following functionality as separate classes/files

* `export-model-versions`
* `import-model-versions`
* `import-registered-models`

2. Append export model versions to `export-registered-models` and then create the corresponding import class/file.  

Would y'all be interested in contributing one or more of these pieces?
Related: https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/issues/2676 - I'll actually close #2676 as a dup of this issue.

@smurching 

Changing the prioritization for this to `important-longterm` anding a `help wanted`.
